`concatMap` is `List.map f ∘ List.foldr (fun x acc => cons x acc) []`.
So, `rw [concatMap]` rewrites the goal using the definition of `concatMap`.
The left side `x :: (concat1 ∘ List.map fromRA.frm) (Digit.zero :: ds)` becomes `x :: List.map fromRA.frm (List.foldr consRA nilRA (Digit.zero :: ds))`.
