The theorem states that for any list `xs`, `xs = fromRA (toRA xs)`. The proof uses induction on `xs`.
- Base case `xs = []`: `x :: [] = fromRA (toRA (x :: []))`. `toRA (x :: [])` is `consRA x (toRA [])`. `toRA []` is `nilRA`. So `toRA (x :: [])` is `consRA x (List.foldr consRA nilRA [])`, which is `consRA x nilRA`. `fromRA (consRA x nilRA)` is `x :: fromRA (List.foldr consRA nilRA [])`. `fromRA (List.foldr consRA nilRA [])` is `fromRA (List.foldr consRA nilRA [])`. This simplifies to `x :: [] = x :: []`, which is true by reflexivity.
